    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Family of around 1,600 genera and 24,000 species of herbs, shrubs, vines, and trees. Members of the family have flower heads composed of many small flowers (florets) surrounded by bracts (leaflike structures), with bell-shaped disk florets forming the center of each head. Fossils suggest that the first members of this family may have evolved in Argentina around 50 million years ago.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000093795/Encyclopedia Britannica Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Familie van ongeveer 1600 genera en 24.000 soorten kruiden, struiken, klimplanten en bomen. De leden van deze familie hebben bloemhoofdjes die bestaan uit een groot aantal kleine klokvormige bloempjes op een schijf met bracteeën (schutbladeren) eromheen. Fossielen wijzen erop dat de eerste leden van deze familie ongeveer 50 miljoen jaar geleden in Argentinië zijn ontstaan.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>包含大約1600個屬、以及24000個草本、藤蔓與喬木物種的屬，該科植物具有由許多小花所組成的頭狀花序，小花由苞片（似葉片的構造）所環繞，每個頭的中心由鈴形盤小花所形成。化石資料顯示，最早的菊科植物可能是在大約5千萬年前的阿根廷所演化而成的。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
